node.text:
Reporting with @baxter on ESPN: The NBA and NBPA continue to negotiate aspects of COVID-related protocols and procedures for the upcoming 2021-22 campaign, but the NBPA has refused to budge on its demand that players not be required to take the vaccine, sources say, and any proposal that mandates vaccination remains a "non-starter."
NBA referees and most NBA staff are mandated to be vaccinated.

node.text:
Restricted free agent F Jarred Vanderbilt (@jvando_ ) has agreed to stay with the Minnesota Timberwolves on a new three-year, $13.8 million deal, his agent Kevin Bradbury of @rep1basketball tells ESPN.

Vanderbilt, 22, played his first injury-free season since his junior year of high school for the Timberwolves. He’s still played fewer than 100 NBA games.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adrian Wojnarowski on September 10, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'wish SHOPPING BREAKING NEWS FROM WOJ'.

node.text:
The Lakers have agreed to trade center Marc Gasol, a 2024 second-round pick and cash to the Grizzlies for the draft rights to Wang Zhelin, sources tell ESPN. Deal saves Lakers $10M in salary and taxes. Gasol and Grizzlies will work together on waiver and release to allow him to remain in Spain with his family. 

The Lakers signed two former All-Star centers this offseason -- Dwight Howard and DeAndre Jordan -- for franchise's frontcourt. Gasol has a one-year, $2.7M that multiplies with Lakers luxury tax. Gasol, 36, is three-time All-Star, an NBA Defensive Player of Year and NBA champion.

Of course, Gasol's Hall of Fame-level career blossomed with a Lakers-Grizzlies trade for his brother Pau in 2008. Marc had a remarkable 11-year run with Memphis. For now, he'll stay in Spain with his family after a release. Memphis grabs another draft asset in the process.

node.text:
Free agent F @alizejohnson24 has agreed to a two-year, $3.6M deal with the Chicago Bulls, his agent @georgelangberg tells ESPN. The Bulls had a need for power forward depth and roster offers some real opportunity for Johnson. He will fill the Bills’ 15th and final roster spot. 
Johnson averaged 5.2 points and 5 rebounds for the Nets last season, including a 20 point, 21 rebound game vs. Indiana.

Pistons plan to work through a buyout on two-years, $20M owed Jordan; Nets will save $47M in salary and tax on deal.'.

node.text:
Pistons plan to work on the buyout with Jordan to allow him to become a free agent, per sources. In that scenario, the Lakers are expected to be a serious contender, per sources. 
Nets send Pistons their own 2022 and 2027 second-round picks, a 2024 second-rounder via Wizards and a 2025 second via Warriors, sources tell ESPN.
Nets have shown ability to recruit top-level vet-minimum talent as a big-market title contender, which alleviates pressure of surrendering picks over life of Durant/Harden/Irving era. $47M in savings can be reinvested into free agents at mid-level exception, buying future seconds.

node.text:
Memphis has agreed to trade forward Juancho Hernangomez to Boston for guards Kris Dunn, Carsen Edwards and a 2026 second-round pick swap, sources tell ESPN.

Deal can’t be completed until September 15, when Dunn and Edwards contracts are allowed to be aggregated in the trade.

Hernangomez gives the Celtics another potential floor-spacer in a bench role; Grizzlies continue to find some value in margins and will continue to be open to deals as franchise manages a roster numbers crunch ahead of 2021-2022 season.
